1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Imitation replays execution; LfO preserves task equivalence.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:22,000
Symbolic teleoperation separates encoding from decoding.

3
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:34,000
High-level intent and local reaction belong on different sides.

4
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Vision can encode intent because force is handled during execution.

5
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Piaget frames skills as internalized action schemas.

6
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Transfer succeeds when representation, grounding, and skill coverage align.

7
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:21,000
The full architecture is observation, task model, skill agents, and feedback.

8
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Generalist behavior factorizes invariants from adaptation.
